- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses high order discretizations, non-smooth multigrid methods, and multiscale methods. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper discusses grid modifications and coupling of domains, which are relevant to computational engineering and science. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses a distributed and unified numerical environment. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the module structure of the Dune framework.
